summary:
A housekeeper was sorting through the paper recycling bins in the parking lot and found a stack of papers containing patient names, SSNs, dates of birth and a list of medications.  10/23/14:
There was information on 106 different Veterans, including full name, patient ID number, date of birth, gender, height, weight, name of medication, prescription number, date filled, total quantity, quantity dispensed, how many and how often to take, provider's name and DEA number, clinic name and date of visit, and the name of the Pharmacist who filled it.
The bins were already outside when the housekeeper found it. The area is accessible to the public.

victim.victim_id: United States Department of Veterans Affairs
